content: Phenomenal. I am no tarot expert but twice in a week the card of the day came literally true. It's packed with features, easy to use, one of the best $3.99 I have ever spent. Helps me up my tarot game considerably.

This app is a great tool for learning the tarot and very useful, especially for beginners. The app itself is very well made and well worth the price. The addition of the books is very valuable as well. The one place I think there is room for improvement is in the books: I'd like it if they were in the main menu instead of buried in the "explore" menu, and I'd love the ability to change the background and font colors for reading in the dark. Even with those suggestions, it's still a 5 star app!

I love the fact there's a new card for each day and there's a widget you can put on your home screen to keep the card of the day top of mind. However, the one down fall I find is that different tarot references for the same cards have different meaning depending on what reference app or website you research. It has made it difficult to learn as I know the creators had one meaning in mind. I'm hoping this is the original meaning of the cards and not just someone else's interpretation. Can anyone confirm or deny?

This has been an enjoyable way to learn the symbols of tarot with a classic deck. This particular artwork never appealed to me as a "hands on" deck,  but i like to study it in comparison to other favorite card decks so i don't lose the original intuitive nuances.  The app works flawlessly in a variety of applications,  spreads and journaling.
